As you can see, with the new changes only configured queue/pg counters are present in the DB and in the telemetry request output.

There is another thing I would like to raise, removing or creating buffer PG/Queue configuration dynamically on runtime will remove/create the corresponding counter for the buffer PG/Queue.
The telemetry module is initializing with the configured counters and will reply to telemetry query requests with this data.
Meaning, dynamically changes will locally delete from the SONiC DB’s , but it will not remove the counter from the telemetry response.
Since the polling thread is killed when the counter is removed, the counter value will not be updated but the entry will still be present in the telemetry output.

